Git init -> initializes a git repository
Git status -> shows you the status of the files
(staging/unstaging)
Git add <file_a> <file_b> -> adds untracked files (adding
files to staging area)
Git commit -> commits files : eg git commit -m “message”
Git log -> showing logs of commits
Git diff -> tells you the diff of files in unstaged area
Git diff --cached -> tells you the diff in the staging ar
